{{Politics of Panama}}
A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in [[Panama]] in 1983.<ref name=N1>[[Dieter Nohlen|Nohlen, D]] (2005) ''Elections in the Americas: A data handbook, Volume I'', p518 {{ISBN|978-0-19-928357-6}}</ref> Voters were asked whether they approved of a series of amendments to the [[Constitution of Panama|1972 constitution]]. A reported 87.8% voted in favour, with a turnout of 66.8%.<ref>Nohlen, p525</ref>
