'''Service ex juris''' is [[Service of process|legal notice]] of an upcoming proceeding given to a defendant who resides outside of the jurisdiction of the court. Rules of service ''ex juris'' are typically found in the rules of [[civil procedure]] and are limited by subject matter and the strength of the connection between the subject and the jurisdiction.
==See also== * [[Long-arm jurisdiction]]
[[Category:Conflict of laws]] [[Category:Civil procedure]] {{law-term-stub}}
